Put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil for the noodles. Remove the root from the @spring onion{2} and thinly slice (keep green and white parts separate). Halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and slice into ½cm strips. Halve, deseed and finely chop the @red chilli{¼}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) and @ginger{½}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

In a small #bowl{}, mix together the @tomato ketchup{½%tbsp}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @sweet chilli sauce{32%ml}, @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @water{2%tbsp} and set aside. Put the @Chinese five spice{1%tsp} and @cornflour{10%g} in a #mixing bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add the @beef strips{240%g} to the cornflour bowl and toss to coat it thoroughly.

> TIP: Use less five spice if you want to keep things subtle!

Add the @egg noodle nest{2} to your pan of boiling water. Cook for ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{}, then refill the pan with cold water and submerge the noodles to stop them cooking further. Set aside until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once almost smoking, carefully add the steak strips to the pan. Cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Don't crowd the pan or your steak will stew not fry! Cook it in batches if necessary.

Once each batch of steak is just crisp around the edges, remove it to rest on some #kitchen paper{}. IMPORTANT: The steak strips are cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Wipe out the pan, pop it back on the heat and add a drizzle of oil, the pepper and a little of the chopped chilli. Cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the garlic, ginger and the whites of the spring onion. Cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the sauce to the veggies and cook until glossy, about ~{1%minute} more.

> TIP: If you don't like heat, go easy on the chilli, or omit it completely and add only at the end for the spice lovers!

Drain the noodles again in the colander and add them to the pan along with the steak strips. Toss everything together and heat through until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide between your plates and serve with the greens of the spring onion scattered over the top. Add any remaining chilli if you like it spicy. Enjoy!